==English==
===Etymology===
From [[w:Clancy of the Overflow|Clancy of the Overflow]], a character in a poem of that name (also in ''[[w:The Man from Snowy River|The Man from Snowy River]]'') by Australian poet [[w:Banjo Patterson|Banjo Patterson]].
===Noun===
# An [[overflow]] or [[spillage]].
#: 1971: ''They'd had a clancy ... He had dozed off with the water running and there was water slopping everywhere.'' &mdash; [[w:David Ireland|David Ireland]], ''The Unknown Industrial Prisoner''